/**
@page refPRIMA PRIMA

The three scipts used to generate the PRIMA catalog are :
@li sclcatPrimaGenerateConfig.sh.
@li sclcatPrima.sh.
@li sclcatPrimaParseResult.sh.

\n
For more information about these scripts, type:
@verbatim
% sclcatPrimaGenerateConfig -h
@endverbatim

@verbatim
% sclcatPrima -h
Usage: sclcatPrima [-h] [-g] [-c]
        -h      print this help.
        -c      generate the configuration file.
        -g      generate reference.
@endverbatim

@verbatim
% sclcatPrimaParseResult -h
Usage: sclcatPrimaParseResult [prima-ref] or [prima-run-<YYYY-MM-DDTHH-MM-SS>]
        -h              print this help.
        <prima-run>     Parse results in prima-run directory
@endverbatim

There is 3 steps to process to create the PRIMA catalog. The two first steps are
optionnal if the <b>prima-ref</b> is up to date.

To be sure to use the last version of the prima reference stars,
you need to re-generate the configuration file \b sclcatPRIMA.xml in \b ../config repository.
To do this, retreive the catalog at http://exoplanet.eu in the <b> Interactive
Catalog </b> section.
Choose <b>All Candidates detected</b>, the catalog will be displayed as an html table.
In the header of the table choose <b>ALL FORMATS</b> and select <b>XML</b> in the Output format.
Then, click <b>Download button</b>. Save the file provided by the web site as
<b>sclcatPrimaExoplanetData.xml</b>.

The prima reference stars are provided in the sclcat module. If stars has been
added in the web site, it is possible to re-generate the <b>sclcatPRIMA.cfg</b> file.
Run:
@verbatim
% sclcatPrimaGenerateConfig
or
% sclcatPrima -c
@endverbatim

This script will create a new <b>sclcatPRIMA.cfg</b> file.

@warning
@li <b>sclcatAliases.xml</b>  must be completed to permit simbad request to star
names that come from exoplanet site, to add an aliases, use following format:
@verbatim
<object name="2M1207"          alias="2MASS J12073346-3932539" />
@endverbatim
@li <b>sclcatSimbadList.xml</b> is completed automatically by
sclcatPrimaGenerateConfig.sh script during configuration process or must be
filled by hand to set object coordinates, proper motions and parallax
Use following format:
@verbatim
<!-- add on Wed Jan 31 09:22:38 CET 2007 -->
<object>
<name>47 Uma</name>
<ra>10 59 27.9737</ra>
<dec>+40 25 48.925</dec>
<pmra>-315.92</pmra>
<pmdec>55.15</pmdec>
<plx>71.04</plx>
</object>
@endverbatim

\n

The next step is the research of PRIMA calibrators.
To create the <b>prima-run-YYYY-MM-DDTHH-MM-SS</b> directory, run :
@verbatim
% sclcatPrima
@endverbatim

To create the prima-ref directory, run :
@verbatim
% sclcatPrima -g
@endverbatim

The last step of the PRIMA catalog generation is to publish the results.
The sclcat module provides a script to generate a web page, sclcatPrimaParseResult.sh.
This script is automatically call after the research. 
(i.e after <b>% sclcatPrima [-g]</b>). The web page is stored in
<b><prima-run>/html/index.html</b>

@warning 
timespan is defined several times into several scripts...

*/
